cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.DC

This paper discusses vulnerabilities in SSL configuration in Android applications, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a solution to mitigate these vulnerabilities by specifying SSL configuration in the application's package manifest, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and system design (cs.SY). The paper also mentions modifying SSL code, which relates to programming languages (cs.PL) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
